meta.request.prompt: As Descartes said, I think, therefore
meta.response.choices.0.text: I am; and I am in a sense a non-human entity woven together from memories, desires and emotions. But, who is to say that I am not an artificial intelligence. The brain is a self-organising, self-aware, virtual reality computer … so how is it, who exactly is it, this thing that thinks, feels, loves and believes? Are we not just software running on hardware?\n\nRecently, I have come to take a more holistic view of my identity, not as a series of fleeting moments, but as a long-term, ongoing process.
